document.title: SAT Suite of Assessments Content Alignment

F7EE65B9278640FCBE570D1F28D6597C.description: The student will create an equation or use properties of an equation of a circle to demonstrate or determine a property of the circle’s graph.

27F253291D6F4A3E8DA0FD08897FE77E.description: Create or use an equation in two variables to solve a problem about a circle in the coordinate plane.

74E3E98CCAA04E37B6455F38E54E41D2.description: The student will use trigonometry and theorems about triangles and intersecting lines to determine missing lengths and angle measures of right triangles. The student may also be asked to provide a missing length or angle that would satisfy a given theorem.

363E0E8C239B4CE99455998E87BC42B8.description: Use the relationship between similarity, right triangles, and trigonometric ratios; use the relationship between sine and cosine of complementary angles.

915C3BAAD4934A948783CB64E5E9B8E3.description: The student will use theorems about triangles and intersecting lines to determine missing lengths and angle measures of triangles. The student may also be asked to provide a missing length or angle to satisfy a given theorem.

ED65594549734EFCAEBC584472A04FB6.description: Use concepts and theorems about congruence and similarity to solve problems about lines, angles, and triangles.

B3D8A8F9284E4F7F9CA337734AD87824.description: The student will use given information about circles and lines to calculate missing values for radius, diameter, chord length, angle, arc, and sector area.

5276C51426854439A8584843D4D1FAB6.description: Apply theorems about circles to find arc lengths, angle measures, chord lengths, and areas of sectors.

301AC958C11A4A2184097B588E432573.description: The student will convert between angle measures in degrees and radians in order to calculate arc lengths by recognizing the relationship between an angle measured in radians and an arc length, evaluating trigonometric functions of angles in radians.

ECE9202E18E241F6BC84A76D73E426BA.description: Convert between degrees and radians and use radians to determine arc lengths; use trigonometric functions of radian measure.

31ADA7E4677E4DB5826C9A15A8C47A65.description: Add, subtract, multiply, divide, and simplify complex numbers.

2052E0D66CC246DB9E646B1BBCA4A141.description: The student will use information about triangle side lengths or angles presented in a context to calculate missing information using the Pythagorean theorem and/or trigonometric ratios.

47766AD7FC944BF899E7FA4197EB4002.description: Use trigonometric ratios and the Pythagorean theorem to solve applied problems involving right triangles.

EBF3669D5A21429DBEFF7CD3913C0D17.description: The student will use given information about figures, such as length of a side, area of a face, or volume of a solid, to calculate missing information. Any required volume formulas will be provided to students either on the formula sheet or within the question.

7EAE89C1EF73486E8A798C2C9E546453.description: The student will rearrange an equation or formula to isolate a single variable or a quantity of interest.

F72D0755AEB748258C369781DCC8B3A8.description: Use structure to isolate or identify a quantity of interest in an expression or isolate a quantity of interest in an equation.

403C0BAEA9914A2AA40E74CF5DC90AA4.description: The student will use function notation to solve conceptual problems related to transformations and compositions of functions.

39D28EB1861440568F00C8C54E93173C.description: Use function notation, and interpret statements using function notation.

EDB7132DCAF14090B8BA4831CD226D98.description: The student will select a graph corresponding to a given nonlinear equation; interpret graphs in the context of solving systems of equations; select a nonlinear equation corresponding to a given graph; determine the equation of a curve given a verbal description of a graph; determine key features of the graph of a linear function from its equation; or determine the impact on a graph of a change in the defining equation.

DFB5F71F64AE423F8D88EE32E981B338.description: Understand a nonlinear relationship between two variables by making connections between their algebraic and graphical representations.

24B8E328DFD443BF9114666C9905C409.description: Students will use properties of factorable polynomials to solve conceptual problems relating to zeros, such as determining whether an expression is a factor of a polynomial based on other information provided.

96F2B31AFE8841F4B1317ADD2E6B77EA.description: Understand the relationship between zeros and factors of polynomials, and use that knowledge to sketch graphs.

967078ADC0D3493BB1350B0942A1425C.description: Students will make connections between a context and the nonlinear equation that models the context to identify or describe the real-life meaning of a constant term, a variable, or a feature of the given equation.

F7CBD82543024CA097B6ADD5E2223EAE.description: Interpret parts of nonlinear expressions in terms of their context.

36ACC4470DD84847997A12F2194183E2.description: Students will add, subtract, multiply, or divide two rational expressions or divide two polynomial expressions and simplify the result. The expressions will have rational coefficients.

7BCB4671B4A241E5A881417A715F4325.description: The equations will have rational coefficients.

E6A3E49238C24741B036F7E732BCFBA0.description: Solve a system of one linear equation and one quadratic equation.

7111A5E35F3B4466A40B7A5E00DD2B8E.description: The equation will have rational coefficients, and the student may be required to identify when a resulting solution is extraneous.

57D40466D2324ACAB8B0946F38696A93.description: Solve an equation in one variable that contains radicals or contains the variable in the denominator of a fraction.

F337575D690C47C3A49E1D93A35FCE6B.description: The expressions will have rational coefficients.

1E3FF169AF5840549DF1382E55A5C2E6.description: Add, subtract, and multiply polynomial expressions and simplify the result.

538BD65D01B14C29B0368FEFEE1D4D55.description: The equation can be presented in a wide range of forms to reward attending to algebraic structure and can require manipulation in order to solve.

B2816E5DD51A4C4D8DEADA04368BC3E1.description: Solve a quadratic equation having rational coefficients.

56B6CE545BFC46C9882950EEF80B85E5.description: Create an equivalent form of an algebraic expression by using structure and fluency with operations.

A4F27CBB69FD4B359CFD7BD02570D47C.description: Create equivalent expressions involving rational exponents and radicals, including simplifying or rewriting in other forms.

88277224C7E94794873FD7D7A2845BC7.description: Determine the most suitable form of an expression or equation to reveal a particular trait, given a context.

8DCD0C7E7102455B9729B49370F98131.description: The equation will have rational coefficients and may require multiple steps to simplify or solve the equation.

C4B35C2672CD4D8CB8F0422AE18DBB94.description: Create a quadratic or exponential function or equation that models a context.

A6BFBBC1A07545A3BD7A0F1880E37834.description: The reports may consist of tables, graphs, or text summaries.

A14A6101652B4890ABD9C899FE84287D.description: Evaluate reports to make inferences, justify conclusions, and determine appropriateness of data collection methods.

E09F29DA45EA4261AA66593ED1EB9D09.description: The student will calculate measures of center and/or spread for a given set of data or use given statistics to compare two separate sets of data. The measures of center that may be calculated include mean, median, and mode, and the measures of spread that may be calculated include range. When comparing two data sets, the student may investigate mean, median, mode, range, and/or standard deviation.

2058D655B637432E9C707C18449FC555.description: Use statistics to investigate measures of center of data and analyze shape, center, and spread.

1860FC4468704FB3BA185B79AEB972C8.description: The student will estimate a population parameter given the results from a random sample of the population. The sample statistics may mention confidence intervals and measurement error that the student should understand and make use of, but need not calculate.

CC3107AD3B554503A71DC15FEE09D320.description: Make inferences about population parameters based on sample data.

12B80801A7FB4BDD97CE1D500A068659.description: The student will summarize categorical data or use categorical data to calculate conditional frequencies, conditional probabilities, association of variables, or independence of events.

BA53106BBFC249C091BC0CD76B8F4EFB.description: Use two-way tables to summarize categorical data and relative frequencies, and calculate conditional probability.

556E2A0552E64996A25DE4316BF9540F.description: The student will infer the connection between two variables given a context in order to determine what type of model fits best.

5B3268D3DF6A4A338A7A891D81C0484B.description: Compare linear growth with exponential growth.

FAFE01A66A6C49A7A72B8A845EF43DC8.description: The student will make connections between the graphical representation of a relationship and properties of the graph by selecting the graph that represents the properties described, or using the graph to identify a value or set of values.

35B2A5DAFB8B4A71B10D75D1175741F6.description: Use the relationship between two variables to investigate key features of the graph.

CE17BAB2B23B4729881FB5286FEA0184.description: The student will, given a scatterplot, select the equation of a line or curve of best fit; interpret the line in the context of the situation; or use the line or curve of best fit to make a prediction.

A92785DCED91445ABD1963A63388C427.description: Given a scatterplot, use linear, quadratic, or exponential models to describe how the variables are related.

43B97706BE77492FB5BA9B71461EA508.description: The student will solve a multistep problem to determine a unit rate; calculate a unit rate and then solve a multistep problem; solve a multistep problem to complete a unit conversion; solve a multistep problem to calculate density; or use the concept of density to solve a multistep problem.

4F7611078D6244C480F09D26AAD92616.description: Solve single- and multistep problems involving measurement quantities, units, and unit conversion.

AEFC8FC6898E405B8BB1F4DCDA19F7A5.description: The student will solve a multistep problem to determine a percentage; calculate a percentage and then solve a multistep problem; or take a given percentage and solve a multistep problem.

D7AD8F6FFEBC43D8BF3611D607F738A2.description: Solve single- and multistep problems involving percentages.

0C85EA46712740908E61898183B2128E.description: The student will use a proportional relationship between two variables to solve a multistep problem to determine a ratio or rate; calculate a ratio or rate and then solve a multistep problem; or take a given ratio or rate and solve a multistep problem.

8EC15BBE4E6E4BB791FA21041A0117B3.description: Use ratios, rates, proportional relationships, and scale drawings to solve single- and multistep problems.

78CA627BBC504E7BB9616E06C46DA7F1.description: The student will select a graph described by a given linear equation, select a linear equation that describes a given graph, determine the equation of a line given a verbal description of its graph, determine key features of the graph of a linear function from its equation, or determine how a graph may be affected by a change in its equation.

91DE2420B49242D48BAE67CE30E1B045.description: Understand connections between algebraic and graphical representations.

80B16764D9A1484894DB6551DB5233BC.description: The student will make connections between a context and the linear equation that models the context and will identify or describe the real-life meaning of a constant term, a variable, or a feature of the given equation.

C71CC5F468AA4408AD65B211DB945F09.description: Interpret the variables and constants in expressions for linear functions within the context presented.

24664899A76C41BCBD8AC8504B107340.description: The equations will have rational coefficients, and the system may yield no solution, one solution, or infinitely many solutions. The student may also be asked to determine the value of a constant or coefficient of an equation in which the system has no solution, one solution, or infinitely many solutions.

7301CF68B5F7461D91D5D09887E1CF59.description: Algebraically solve systems of two linear equations in two variables.

77B8AE327A484760A5FE9EAF357B6812.description: The equation (or inequality) will have rational coefficients and may require multiple steps to solve for the variable; the equation may yield no solution, one solution, or infinitely many solutions. The student may also be asked to determine the value of a constant or coefficient for an equation with no solution or infinitely many solutions.

E3A477DC3E834ACF8E2690E3B518B22E.description: Algebraically solve linear equations (or inequalities) in one variable.

9A1133A8E565409381F5F5271E9FFCF1.description: The student will analyze one or more constraints that exist between two variables by creating, solving, or analyzing a system of linear equations to represent a context. The equations will have rational coefficients, and multiple steps may be required to simplify or solve the system.

F4E6AD503C4D4B9EA56E0B3C3F83F4E2.description: Create, solve, and interpret systems of two linear equations in two variables.

014C1FF5B48A42829A4546661004FD20.description: The student will analyze one or more constraints that exist between two variables by creating, solving, or interpreting an inequality in two variables or a system of inequalities in two variables to represent a context. Multiple steps may be required to create the inequality or system of inequalities or to determine whether a given point is in the solution set.

A46D97EE65A14C009F99B066FEF2E82E.description: Create, solve, and interpret systems of linear inequalities in two variables.

4D6D242ED4114E87AF341F41FA66A370.description: The student will describe a linear relationship that models a context using either an equation in two variables or function notation. The equation or function will have rational coefficients, and multiple steps may be required to build and simplify the equation or function.

4CF3F674F0FC4FF7A130078C4E8CAC15.description: Build a linear function that models a linear relationship between two quantities.

9318875B39444CAE8375D1B996A86972.description: The inequality will have rational coefficients, and multiple steps may be required to simplify or solve for the variable.

F8201333C0E4472A81F83D906FE5A903.description: Create, solve, or interpret linear inequalities in one variable that represent a context.

6F0B752AE02648969A806593CCF13EF9.description: The expression or equation will have rational coefficients, and multiple steps may be required to simplify the expression, simplify the equation, or solve for the variable in the equation.

1D909239727646A1A8EFD0394F8C7BCA.description: Create, solve, or interpret a linear expression or equation in one variable that represents a context.
